      <hedline>
        <hl1>You Won. Now Legislate!</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Fletcher Copp letter, prompted by Jan 28 Frank Rich Op-Ed column, calls for presidential contenders in Congress to work at jobs they were elected to do--legislate</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Frank Rich (column, Jan. 28) got it right: who in Washington will be brave enough to act?</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Frank Rich (column, Jan. 28) got it right: who in Washington will be brave enough to act?</p>
        <p>I suggest that the presidential contenders for 2008, both Democrats and Republicans, do what they were sent to Washington to do -- legislate.</p>
        <p>Waiting for a new president to stop the bloodletting is not what the people mandated in the 2006 elections.</p>
        <p>Fletcher Copp  New York, Jan. 28, 2007</p>
      </block>
